icantly affected aerosol optical depth (AOD) over EA, with the contributions ranged from 0.1 to 0.3 (25%e45% in total AOD) in 2008 to 0.2e0.6 (50%e70% in total AOD) in 2010. Our analysis indicated that although PSEA biomass burning may have relatively stable impact on air quality over EA from year to year, it will cause significant disturbance to the free troposphere over EA for both atmospheric chemistry and radiative forcing budget.";s:11:"article_ref";s:67:"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1352231015301254";s:18:"article_viewscount";s:3:"124";s:17:"article_timestamp";s:19:"2018-05-06 20:30:00";s:14:"article_status";s:1:"1";}i:156;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:10:"article_id";s:2:"54";s:13:"article_title";s:128:"Trends in black carbon and size-resolved particle number concentrations and vehicle emission factors under real-world conditions";s:14:"article_author";s:88:"Krecl, Patricia
